display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longrightarrow )]]></fr:tex> Assume <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> is irreducible and assume <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(a)]]></fr:tex> is a proper principal ideal of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> (for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  R]]></fr:tex>). Then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {align*} (p)\subseteq  (a) &\iff  p\in (a)\\ &\iff  p=ab\hbox { for some }b\in  R\\ &\implies  a\mathrel {\bigm |} p\\ &\implies  a=pu\hbox { or }a=u\hbox { for some unit }u\in R^{\times }\end {align*}]]></fr:tex>
If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a=u]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(a)=R]]></fr:tex> which contradicts our assumption that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(a)]]></fr:tex> is proper.</fr:p>
<fr:p>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a=pu]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(a)=(p)]]></fr:tex>, hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(p)]]></fr:tex> is maximal among proper principal ideals.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longleftarrow )]]></fr:tex> Suppose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(p)]]></fr:tex> is maximal among principal proper ideals. We want to show <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> is irreducible. Suppose there exists some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  R]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {\bigm |} p]]></fr:tex>, which is equivalent to saying <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(a)\subseteq (p)]]></fr:tex>. Then either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(a)=R]]></fr:tex> (which means <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in R^{\times }]]></fr:tex> is a unit) or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(a)=(p)]]></fr:tex> (which implies <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a=pu]]></fr:tex> for some unit <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in R^{\times }]]></fr:tex>). In both cases, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> is irreducible.</fr:p><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
